<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-07-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-07-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="415" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d415">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 7357/185.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Dodge</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">San
                                        Salvador</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-07-28"><hi rend="italic">July 28,
                                1908</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. Dodge states that the consul at Tegucigalpa reports the cancellation
                            by the Honduranean Government of the exequaturs of the American consul
                            and vice consul at Ceiba, as well as that of the French consular agent.
                            Mr. Dodge says no reason is given for this step, but it is presumably on
                            account of the action lately taken by the consular officials mentioned,
                            which was previously reported to department by the consul.</p>
                    </div>
